
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pkix-caa-15.pdf'>
    <title>"DNS Certification Authority Authorization (CAA) Resource Record", Phillip Hallam-Baker, Rob Stradling</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-pkix-caa-15.pdf</link>
    <description>The Certification Authority Authorization (CAA) DNS Resource Record allows a DNS domain name holder to specify one or more Certification Authorities (CAs) authorized to issue certificates for that domain. CAA resource records allow a public Certification Authority to implement additional controls to reduce the risk of unintended certificate mis-issue.  This document defines the syntax of the CAA record and rules for processing CAA records by certificate issuers.</description>
    <dc:date>2012-10-17T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
